# Java Import Rules

Use the repository `.editorconfig` as the source of truth for Java import layout and ordering.

## Required

- Use explicit single-class imports only.
- Use explicit static imports only.
- Keep static imports in a separate block.
- Preserve the repository-defined import group order.
- Resolve ambiguous type names deliberately.
- Ensure imports are compile-clean after editing.
- Use fully qualified names only when an ambiguity cannot be resolved cleanly through imports.

Explicit static imports are allowed in tests for JUnit, AssertJ, Mockito, and other approved test libraries.

## Forbidden

Do not use:

```java
import java.util.*;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;
import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.*;
```

Do not:

- introduce wildcard imports
- introduce static wildcard imports
- reorder imports in unrelated files
- modify a file only to optimize or reformat imports
- create import-only churn
- accept generated imports without compilation verification
- guess between ambiguous classes based only on a simple name

## Ambiguous Types

Pay special attention to names such as:

- `Context`
- `Span`
- `Scope`
- `Attributes`
- `Date`
- `Duration`
- `Configuration`
- `Status`
- `TraceContext`
- `ValidationResult`
- `ControlResult`
- `RuntimePolicy`

Inspect the owning package and existing module conventions before choosing an import.

Do not replace a correct domain type merely to avoid an import conflict.

## Expected Grouping

Follow `.editorconfig`. The intended high-level grouping is:

```java
import static ...;

import java...;
import javax...;
import jakarta...;

import org...;

import com...;

import space...;

import ...;
```

Do not force this example over a different layout explicitly configured by the repository.

## Scope Discipline

When editing a Java file:

- update imports only as required by the semantic change
- remove imports made unused by that change
- preserve unrelated import ordering
- do not run repository-wide import optimization as part of a focused task
- do not include import-only changes in unrelated files

## Verification

After editing Java files, run the narrowest relevant tasks:

```powershell
.\gradlew.bat :<affected-module>:compileJava --no-daemon
.\gradlew.bat :<affected-module>:compileTestJava --no-daemon
```

Run the affected tests when test or production behavior changed.

If the repository has a wildcard-import or formatting gate, run it as well.

Do not report import cleanup as complete when the affected source set has not compiled.
